10/02/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Greece, the 2004 European football champion, is again in the running for a slot in the 2006 World Cup after a 2-1 victory over Denmark in Athens on Wednesday (9 February). Group II leader Ukraine defeated Albania in Tirana 2-0 and is six points ahead of Greece. In a Group I match in Skopje, the amateur team of Andorra held Macedonia to a goalless draw. In friendly games this week, Bulgaria and Serbia-Montenegro drew 0-0 in Sofia, Israel held visiting Croatia to a 3-3 draw, and Slovakia and Romania ended their game in a 2-2 draw. (AP, AFP, Reuters - 09/02/05) 
